        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Curacao</placeName> <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March 1853</date></p>
			<p>To the <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">As <persName>Mr. Elias Lindo</persName>&#44; has<lb/> just received a letter for Ocean Bird&#44; from <persName>Mr Seixas</persName> of <placeName>N Y</placeName>&#44;<lb/> acknowledging the receipt of the Box of Books and as <persName>Mr E.<lb/> Lindo</persName> himself has written to you&#44; long since&#44; explaining the<lb/> cause of its detention&#44; there appears no necessity for my saying<lb/> any thing further on the subject&#44; than to regret the annoyance<lb/> it has occasioned you.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">In a very short time I hope to have the pleasure<lb/> of sending you for insertion in the Occident&#44; an account of<lb/> the formation of a Hebrew benevolent society in this <placeName>Island</placeName><lb/> The matter is yet in embargo&#44; only one preliminary meeting having<lb/> as yet been held. As to the account of the founding of the<lb/> Synagogue&#44; I regret to add&#44; that it is beyond my power to furnish<lb/> it&#44; <persName>Mr Miranda</persName> the Secretary <add>&#63;</add>&#44; that the editor<lb/> of the &#8220;Archives Israelites&#8221; applied to him for similar information<lb/> which he was unable to send&#44; in consequence of the Records and<lb/> Books being completely destroyed <del>dest</del> by Ants&#44; and the dampness<lb/> of the climate. I am indebted to you for 1 doz Catechisms&#44; &#8220;Road to faith&#8221;<lb/> but the price for which I have forgotten&#44; send it on if you please&#44; and<lb/> I will send it together with the Amot&#44; of the subscription for the<lb/> Occident&#44; from myself and others. I have only succeeded in</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>in obtaining one more subscriber <persName>Mr E Edwards</persName>&#44; but at the same<lb/> time have prevented another from giving it up. Allow me to<lb/> observe that&#44; wordy warfare such as is contained in your last No.<lb/> is any thing but agreeable or interesting to your Readers in this<lb/> little <placeName>Island</placeName>&#44; and I also think&#44; you lower your own dignity<lb/> by waging it with such an antagonist as <persName>Mr S Jacobs</persName><lb/> This is <hi rend="underline">entre nous</hi>&#44; if he is the same man who was lately in <placeName>Kingston<lb/> Jamaica</placeName>&#44; Make a diligent <sic>enquiry</sic>&#44; and you will find I have<lb/> just grounds for my advice. I must confess&#44; I am taking<lb/> a great liberty with you&#44; but I feel an interest in the success<lb/> of your undertakings&#44; Every prudent man ought to examine<lb/> well&#44; whether he is going to attack a Bee Hive or a Hornet&#39;s Nest<lb/> with kind regard and hoping you are well</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">I am</p>
          <p rend="indent(9)">yours truly</p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author"><add>&#63;</add> Nathan</persName></p>
			<p>PS. Excuse any illegible writing I can only find time<lb/> to write in the evening and my sight fails me at candle<lb/> light</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
